<br>
I hope you don't mind me posting here, but the people at Verant read this board and don't seem to be aware of our chanter boards over at caster's realm.<br>
<br>
The enchanter nuke upgrade, Dementing Visions, has about a 1 in 20 chance of dropping from two highly contested mobs: Tormax and Aaryonar.  This makes the spell more rare than most ancient spells.<br>
<br>
The recent improvements to this spell mean nothing except to a tiny percentage of enchanters on any server.  <br>
<br>
The enchanter community, which has a board located here: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://forums.crgaming.com/eqbb/index.php?h=2&pf=321">forums.crgaming.com/eqbb/...h=2&pf=321</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> , would like an explanation for the rarity of this spell and why modifictions to this spell are being made in the name of class balancing when so few enchanters will ever see it.<br>
<br>
Thanks for your time!<br>
<br>
Cafu<br>
Phantasmist <br>
Prexus<br>
<br>
