</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucantatus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cantatus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/17/02 11:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanter balancing - drop rate of Dementing Visions</span><hr size=1> To be fair, the board has had one post from the Verant staff in the three years I've been going there.  It was about a month ago from Hammerfel about the PoP storyline being added.<br>
<br>
I know Verant doesn't go around posting on the message board on a daily basis, but 1 time in 3 years about something that doesn't even pertain to the class is a little.. lacking to say the least.  EQBeastlord has had more posts in that time.<br>
<br>
Sort of wish one of the Enchanter EZBoard's would take off just so we knew Verant was paying as much attention to our class board as to others.  But, habit is hard to break after 3 years. <p><div align="Center"><img src="http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/csig.jpg" alt="Cantatus - Phantasmist and Artisan of the Karana Server" width="253" height="75">
